I agree, my last pregnancy I had a TON of cramping and every symptom possible, this pregnancy I've had literally nothing except heartburn, I'm 20+1 now and feeling kicks, otherwise I'd forget. I wouldn't worry about it, every pregnancy is different! :)

My first pregnancy was like yours, sick and complications beyond belief. This pregnancy, very few sick days, just severe headaches. I'm 30 weeks and having a healthy baby boy! Every pregnancy is different! I am living proof of that after beating hyperemesis and diabetes in this pregnancy. Good luck!

question: I've been pregnant once before and was really sick to the point I'd stay in bed, sensitive to smell,moody, headaches, excessive sleeping etc. Now I have taken two test and they're showing I am pregnant but I have cramps some headaches but not much more. I'm worried. Is there something wrong? I have missed my cycle but this is exactly the opposite of what I experienced last time. Help!
title: Whats wrong?
